# Key Capture Conflicts on Source Identity and Cursor

## Step

Extends [Patch the Capture Client and Make Replay Canonical](./patch-capture-and-replay.svx): the reboot-fallout session proved ack-loss after server commit defeats run-keyed conflict detection ([root cause](../reboot-hardening/asset-capture-replay-root-cause.svx), `32e6e13a`) — the client, having no pending entry, retries the wider range under a fresh `run_id` and the overlap is stored. Our growth alert caught it live (~90 sources). Resolved when:

1. `run-capture.ts` keys conflict detection on `(source_identity, from_offset)`: any post matching an existing blob's start takes the prefix-resync path regardless of `run_id` — existing-prefix answers ok + existing `to_offset` (client advances, re-sends remainder); non-prefix mismatch stays a hard conflict.
2. The ack-ambiguous client path is hardened too: a timeout/lost-ack writes the pending entry so a retained `run_id` rides retries (belt to the server's braces). If a client path truly cannot know, document why.
3. The `memory/run.captured` consumer (session-index append) treats `(source_identity, from_offset)` as identity so a duplicate overlapping Run can never re-inflate `sessions.db` even if one slips through.
4. Fixture tests replay the exact live failure: commit → lost ack → wider retry under fresh `run_id` → server answers resync, index stores once. Plus the legitimate flows (suffix Runs, `accepted_prefix`) stay green.

Containment as always: raw JSONL immutable, no live backlog replay in this step, no worker restart (steering deploys), do not commit.

